        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 30 at 6:13AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 613 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gladewater, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Longview, White Oak, Gladewater, Ore City, Clarksville City, East
Mountain, West Mountain, Diana, Liberty City, Union Grove, Warren
City and Judson.
</description>
